text: Mount Banahaw, is a potentially active volcano in the Philippines, situated at the vicinity of the towns in Lucban, Quezon and Majayjay, Laguna. https://www.phivolcs.dost.gov.ph/index.php/volcano-hazard/volcanoes-of-the- philippines It is surrounding by the inactive volcanoes, The Laguna Volcanic Field to the west and Laguna Caldera to the north. ==Reference== Category:Volcanoes of the Philippines
title: Mount Banahaw
